## Layer Splitting

### Standard 4-Layer Structure

Every illustration gets split into these 4 layers + 1 fallback:

| Layer | Filename | Content |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Background | `<name>-background.svg` | Environment, clouds, ground, structures |
| Accent | `<name>-accent.svg` | Neon energy, glows, highlights (`#CCFF00`) |
| Figure | `<name>-figure.svg` | Main character body + outlines |
| Foreground | `<name>-foreground.svg` | White highlights, small details |
| **Fallback** | `<name>.svg` | Complete combined illustration |

### How to Split

1. Read the SVG and identify paths by `fill` color
2. Group paths into layers based on color mapping above
3. Create 4 new files with same `viewBox`, each containing only relevant `<path>` elements
4. Keep original as fallback

### Folder Structure

```
Zeno/Resources/SVGs/
└── <illustration-name>/
    ├── <name>.svg              ← Fallback
    ├── <name>-background.svg
    ├── <name>-accent.svg
    ├── <name>-figure.svg
    └── <name>-foreground.svg
```

